editableNewDialogue.text:
{
  "Name": "Loop URLs Skeleton",
  "Commands": [
    {"Command":"store","Target":"0","Value":"i"},
    {"Command":"storeJson","Target":"[\"https://example.com/1\",\"https://example.com/2\"]","Value":"urls"},
    {"Command":"while","Target":"${i} < ${urls}.length"},

    {"Command":"open","Target":"${urls}[${i}]"},

    {"Command":"comment","Target":"--- paste your per-page steps here ---"},

    {"Command":"executeScript","Target":"return Number(${i}) + 1;","Value":"i"},
    {"Command":"end"}
  ]
}
Notes: names like storeJson/while/end vary by tool; if your runner doesn’t support JSON arrays, you can use a delimited string and split via executeScript.
